The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 22 February is 223,085 (25,711.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 17 February, there were 6,462 new confirmed cases (744.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 10 February, there were 8,245 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 22% (1,783 fewer cases).
